properties.areaDesc: Southeast Johnson County; Northeast Johnson County
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 6 at 3:05PM MST until February 7 at 11:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...Moderate to heavy snow and wind will impact western and
northern Wyoming through Friday...

.Snow will continue in the west tonight through Friday morning.
Snow will continue in the north and central tonight into Friday
morning. Moderate to heavy snow will occur in the Bighorn
mountains. Southern Lincoln county will see strong wind gusts
along with the light snow creating blowing snow issues for
travelers.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches
along with 4 to 6 inches of storm total snow. Winds gusting as
high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Northeast Johnson County and Southeast Johnson County.

* WHEN...Through 11 AM MST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult including travel on
Interstates 25 and 90. The hazardous conditions could impact
the evening and morning commute, including along Highway 14/16.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM MST FRIDAY
